{"key":"processedPost-10614586","value":{"id":10614586,"first":10610031,"last":10615730,"when":1246631008,"utime":"07/03/09 05:23 PM","cleanedPost":"Normally, fruit size is related to substrate moisture content.&nbsp; Try lifting the cakes and you can judge moisture level by how much they weigh.&nbsp; It takes a few grows to get the feel for it, but next time you birth/dunk and roll, pay attention to how heavy the cakes are.&nbsp; If you suspect they're drying out later, you can lift one and tell right away.&nbsp; You can also set cakes in a saucer of water overnight mid-flush.<br />I should mention that waterlogged cakes will also perform poorly and have small fruits.&nbsp; You have to find that happy spot in the middle.<br />RR"}}